People3
\kingThis is the Chamber of the Seal.
People3
\kingAll that separates us from \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] is this door.
People3
\kingThat is... if \c[18]he\c[0]'s even in there.
People3
\king\N[1], do you think I'm... crazy?
People3
\kingI just try my hardest to help my kingdom.
People3
\kingI want everyone in the Overworld to feel
safe. But with everything that goes on day
to day, that's just not possible.
People3
\kingI really do try my hardest... and
sometimes, the stress of this job
gets to me.
People3
\kingI've... always lacked the proper amount of sleep.
People3
\kingI work day and night to keep this kingdom
alive and prospering, and anytime I'm not
working, I just feel... like I'm not doing
my job.
People3
\kingIs this just who I am, \N[1]? Am
I bound to always be fearful of
something happening the moment
I step out of the throne room?
People3
\kingEven now, I wonder... what if someone
is up there, waiting for me to talk to
them? Alfred is there to help... but
still. I just... I don't know.
People3
\kingThis has been our best bet. But if
\c[18]he\c[0]'s not in here... what's next?
People3
\kingHopefully we don't have to worry about that.
CAM PLAYER 1600
People3
\kingOut of all the champions, I trust you
four the most. By far. Your level of
skill and dedication is not even
comparable to these other parties.
People3
\kingIt's not that they're incompetent. I wouldn't be
sending them in here tomorrow if I didn't think they
could hold up in battle. But... you four are just
the strongest adventurers I've seen in a long time.
People3
\kingIn the corner of this room is a chest.
It was prepared when the champion program
was first founded about fifteen years ago.
People3
\kingIn there is several sets of very powerful
armor made of tellurium. Tellurium is a rare
ore that was once in abundance on the continent.
Sadly, we mined most of it a long time ago.
People3
\kingThere's also a set of new clothing you
can wear over your armor. I would like it
if you four wore these new clothes at the
final ceremony tomorrow.
People3
\kingGo to the chest, take out your corresponding
armor and outfits... and then, head to bed.
People3
\kingThank you four for everything. Tomorrow
is the big day. The biggest day of ALL of
our lives.
People3
\kingAs you leave... \N[1], please stay back for a moment.
People3
\kingThere is one more verse of the prophecy.
People3
\kingI came down to these excavations myself,
and when I saw that stone tablet, I pocketed
it. I don't know why I kept this so secretive,
but this information just felt confidential.
People3
\kingThis verse... it's the only one I
believe in. I haven't modified it at
all. This verse...
People3
\king...it states that one day, there will
be another knight who will wield the
legendary blade used by the First Knight.
People3
\kingAnd this blade... it's the only
true, surefire way to seal away
\c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] once and for all.
People3
\king...
People3
\kingMakes it seem like any efforts tomorrow
will be futile, right? Well... I still
think we should try.
People3
\king\c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] won't be at
his full power, after all, so
that might give us the upper
hand we desperately need.
People3
\kingIt's too late to look for this sword, but
if this doesn't quite work out as we plan,
and you manage to make it out alive, looking
for this weapon should become a priority.

People3
\kingAnd speaking of making it out, I
would recommend being very, very
prepared before coming back to the
throne room tomorrow morning.
People3
\kingYou might be... stuck in there for a while.
People3
\kingThank you, \N[1]. See you in the throne room tomorrow.
